text.tspan: Sex ratio at birth vs. at five years old, 2021
Sex ratio at birth, measured as the number of male births per 100 female births versus the sex ratio at five years
old, measured as the number of males per 100 females. The grey line represents the point of equal ratio: countries
which lie above this line had a higher sex ratio at birth than at five years old.
Data source: OWID based on UN (2022)
